I love this cake. The cooks who thought the apple taste didn't come through may not have sauteed the apples long enough. 5-7 minutes is not long enough on my range. It takes more like 15 minutes on low-medium flame, until the apple slices are truly golden brown and maybe are forming a bit of a crunchy crust (be careful not to let them burn). The extensive sauteeing carmelizes the apples and really brings out their flavor.

