Rating: 4
Well this is the apple cake recipe for the permanent file. This is the type of recipe that you steal from your Grandmother's hidden recipe files, covered in smears of cinnamon and touches of batter. I love the fact that it is put together in one bowl, with a whisk. No electric mixers or fancy steps. I read the reviews and went with a 9-inch by 3-inch round cake pan. I lined it (Maida Heatter style) with foil that was lightly sprayed with cooking oil. This way the cake cooled in the pan for 30 minutes, then I lifted it out to a cooling rack. I also topped it with a favorite streusel topping and it was the perfect touch to a lovely cake. Sweet, filled with apple chunks, but not too sweet or too spicy. A keeper. Perfect with a tall glass of milk, or even fancy enough to serve with coffee and tea.

